<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch off.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Disconnect the negative (-) terminal cable from the battery, and wait for at least 90 seconds.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the connector to the combination meter assembly.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the negative (-) terminal cable to the battery, and wait for at least 2 seconds.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG).</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Check the SRS warning light condition.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>After the primary check period, SRS warning light goes off for approximately 10 seconds, and remains on.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<atten4>
<ptxt>The primary check period shows approximately 6 seconds after the ignition switch is turned on (IG).</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test1>
